  "texts": [
    "Graph neural network research evolutionGraph neural networks (GNNs) were first proposed in 2005, but only recently have they begun to gain traction.",
    "GNNs were first introduced by Gori [2005] and Scarselli [2004 Scarselli [, 2009]].",
    "A node's attributes and connected nodes in the graph serve as its natural definitions.",
    "A GNN aims to learn a state embedding h v ε R s that encapsulates each node's neighborhood data.",
    "The distribution of the expected node label is one example of the output."
  ]
}